  <front>
   <head>SCHOOL RHYMES FOR NEGRO CHILDREN.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="sestet">
     <l n="1" met="-+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="11">happy are we in that hour we love,</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="11">When shadows grow longer and branches move;</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|--+|--+" line_length="8">Blithe urchins then we be!</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="11">From the school's low porch with a joyous shout,</l>
     <l n="5" met="-+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="11">We rush and we run and we gambol about,</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|--+|--+" line_length="8">So careless, light and free!</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="sestet">
     <l n="7" met="-+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="11">And the good child merrily plays his part,</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="11">For all is well in his guileless heart,</l>
     <l n="9" met="-+|--+|--+" line_length="8">The glance of his eye is bright.</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="11">We hop and we leap and we toss the ball;</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="11">Some dance to their shadows upon the wall,</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|--+|--+" line_length="8">And spread out their hands with delight.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="3" stanza_type="sestet">
     <l n="13" met="-+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="11">The parrot that sits on her bough a-swinging,</l>
     <l n="14" met="-+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="11">The bird and the butterfly, light air winging,</l>
     <l n="15" met="-+|--+|--+" line_length="8">Are scarcely more happy, I trow.</l>
     <l n="16" met="-+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="11">Then hey for the meadow, the glade and the grove,</l>
     <l n="17" met="-+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="11">For evening is coming and branches move,</l>
     <l n="18" met="-+|--+|--+" line_length="8">We'll have merry pastime now.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
